         b"'http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/n.lathia' rel='external nofollow' cla"
         b'ss=\'url\'>Neal Lathia</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>\t'
         b'\t</div>\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a hr'
         b'ef="http://mobblog.cs.ucl.ac.uk/2007/11/22/recommendation-or-spam/#c'
         b'omment-1312">\n\t\t\tNovember 23, 2007 at 12:42 am</a>\t\t</div>\n\n'
         b'\t\t<p>I think that one of the problems here is explained in this '
         b'paper <a href="http://smg.media.mit.edu/papers/Zinman/britneyspears.'
         b'pdf" rel="nofollow">Is Britney Spears Spam?</a> So, as you said, som'
         b'e people in my social network might not want to hear about my latest'
         b' blockbuster rental; they would classify it as spam. Other people, h'
         b'owever, may be interested in that information. After all, editorial '
         b'movie/music/product reviews are present in the media because people '
         b'value that information. Social networks are simply a medium for ever'
         b'y individual to become a &#8220;reviewer,&#8221; and perhaps the peo'
         b'ple around me will value my opinion.. after all, they are my friends'
         b'!</p>\n<p>The main point is that in this scenario the definition '
         b'of what constitutes spam becomes subjective, and the spam filters sh'
         b'ould operate accordingly. A similar example is facebook&#8217;s late'
         b'st digg-like attempt at customising each user&#8217;s newsfeed.<'
         b'/p>\n<p>It is also arguable that a product endorsement by one of '
         b'my connections does not constitute a recommendation <img src="http:/'
         b'/mobblog.cs.ucl.ac.uk/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt='
         b'";)" class="wp-smiley" />  just like one of my friends wearing a bra'
         b'nd X t-shirt is not a recommendation for me to wear one too; the tru'
         b'e recommendation comes from a (query-less) search by the user that i'
         b's responded to with results that are tailored to his/her tastes (me '
         b'going into a clothes shop, looking at t-shirts, and being recommende'
         b'd brand X). Maybe the question is- are advertisements recommendation'
         b's? I don&#8217;t think so- they are broadcast out to people who fit '
         b'into categories, not made for only me.</p>\n<p>Thoughts?</p>\n'
         b'\n\t\t<div class="reply">\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t'
